  "comment_text": {
    "sn2.6:1.2": "Kāmada, the “granter of pleasure” is otherwise unknown in early texts, but later is an epithet of the Sun or of Shiva. More likely, given that <i lang='pi' translate='no'>kāmada</i> has the same sense as the names in the previous Suttas, it is once more Indra under another name. ",
    "sn2.6:2.3": ""
  },
