  "root_text": {
    "sn2.6:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 2.6 ",
    "sn2.6:0.2": "1. Paṭhamavagga ",
    "sn2.6:0.3": "Kāmadasutta ",
    "sn2.6:1.1": "Sāvatthinidānaṁ. ",
    "sn2.6:1.2": "Ekamantaṁ ṭhito kho kāmado devaputto bhagavantaṁ etadavoca: ",
    "sn2.6:1.3": "“dukkaraṁ, bhagavā, sudukkaraṁ, bhagavā”ti. ",
    "sn2.6:2.1": "“Dukkaraṁ vāpi karonti, ",
    "sn2.6:2.2": "(kāmadāti bhagavā) ",
    "sn2.6:2.3": "Sekhā sīlasamāhitā; ",
    "sn2.6:2.4": "Ṭhitattā anagāriyupetassa, ",
    "sn2.6:2.5": "Tuṭṭhi hoti sukhāvahā”ti. ",
    "sn2.6:3.1": "“Dullabhā, bhagavā, yadidaṁ tuṭṭhī”ti. ",
    "sn2.6:4.1": "“Dullabhaṁ vāpi labhanti, ",
    "sn2.6:4.2": "(kāmadāti bhagavā) ",
    "sn2.6:4.3": "Cittavūpasame ratā; ",
    "sn2.6:4.4": "Yesaṁ divā ca ratto ca, ",
    "sn2.6:4.5": "Bhāvanāya rato mano”ti. ",
    "sn2.6:5.1": "“Dussamādahaṁ, bhagavā, yadidaṁ cittan”ti. ",
    "sn2.6:6.1": "“Dussamādahaṁ vāpi samādahanti, ",
    "sn2.6:6.2": "(kāmadāti bhagavā) ",
    "sn2.6:6.3": "Indriyūpasame ratā; ",
    "sn2.6:6.4": "Te chetvā maccuno jālaṁ, ",
    "sn2.6:6.5": "Ariyā gacchanti kāmadā”ti. ",
    "sn2.6:7.1": "“Duggamo, bhagavā, visamo maggo”ti. ",
    "sn2.6:8.1": "“Duggame visame vāpi, ",
    "sn2.6:8.2": "Ariyā gacchanti kāmada; ",
    "sn2.6:8.3": "Anariyā visame magge, ",
    "sn2.6:8.4": "Papatanti avaṁsirā; ",
    "sn2.6:8.5": "Ariyānaṁ samo maggo, ",
    "sn2.6:8.6": "Ariyā hi visame samā”ti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn2.6:0.1": "Linked Discourses 2.6 ",
    "sn2.6:0.2": "Chapter One ",
    "sn2.6:0.3": "With Kāmada ",
    "sn2.6:1.1": "At Sāvatthī. ",
    "sn2.6:1.2": "Standing to one side, the godling Kāmada said to the Buddha, ",
    "sn2.6:1.3": "“It’s too hard, Blessed One! It’s just too hard!” ",
    "sn2.6:2.1": "“They do it even though it’s hard,” ",
    "sn2.6:2.2": "said the Buddha to Kāmada, ",
    "sn2.6:2.3": "“the stable trainees with ethics, and immersion. ",
    "sn2.6:2.4": "For one who has entered the homeless life, ",
    "sn2.6:2.5": "contentment brings happiness.” ",
    "sn2.6:3.1": "“Such contentment, Blessed One, is hard to find.” ",
    "sn2.6:4.1": "“They find it even though it’s hard,” ",
    "sn2.6:4.2": "said the Buddha to Kāmada, ",
    "sn2.6:4.3": "“those who love peace of mind; ",
    "sn2.6:4.4": "whose minds love to meditate ",
    "sn2.6:4.5": "day and night.” ",
    "sn2.6:5.1": "“But it’s hard, Blessed One, to immerse this mind in samādhi.” ",
    "sn2.6:6.1": "“They become immersed in samādhi <j>even though it’s hard,” ",
    "sn2.6:6.2": "said the Buddha to Kāmada, ",
    "sn2.6:6.3": "“those who love calming the faculties. ",
    "sn2.6:6.4": "Having cut through the net of Death, ",
    "sn2.6:6.5": "the noble ones, Kāmada, go on their way.” ",
    "sn2.6:7.1": "“But this path, Blessed One, is rough and hard to travel.” ",
    "sn2.6:8.1": "“Though it’s rough, hard to travel, ",
    "sn2.6:8.2": "the noble ones, Kāmada, go on their way. ",
    "sn2.6:8.3": "The ignoble fall headfirst ",
    "sn2.6:8.4": "on a rough path. ",
    "sn2.6:8.5": "But the path of the noble ones is smooth, ",
    "sn2.6:8.6": "for the noble ones are smooth amid the rough.” "
  },
